msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:6
msgid ""
"Organizing a PyLadies group is *hard* work, and often under-appreciated. "
"Here are some ways to recognize the signs of burnout, and ways to "
"prevent, deal with, or otherwise alleviate it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:9
msgid "Causes of Burnout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:11
msgid "Your group may be growing faster than anticipated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:12
msgid ""
"Your passion for the community comes with an inability to say no when "
"asked to do things."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:13
msgid ""
"It's exhausting to be \"on\" for so long -- from the preparation leading "
"up to an event, to organizing and interacting with all the people who "
"come to the event, to following up with folks afterward."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:17
msgid "Signs of burnout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:18
msgid ""
"You begin dropping the ball here and there because you've overcommitted "
"to things."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:19
msgid "You begin to dread planning or attending events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:20
msgid "Relationships between organizers deteriorate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:21
msgid "Your initial feeling of goodwill toward attendees begins to sour."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:25
msgid "Ways to prevent burnout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:28
msgid "Running your Group"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:29
msgid ""
"Find co-organizers to help shoulder the burden. We all have different "
"skills, strengths, and weaknesses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:30
msgid ""
"Ask participants to be mentors to beginners. Even beginners can step up "
"to deal with non-technical aspects of an event. This can also make things"
" more fun, and helps build community."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:31
msgid ""
"If people demand even more of you than what they're getting, politely "
"remind them that we don't get paid for this, and that organizers lead "
"*very* busy lives. Suggest that person step up and organize something "
"themselves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:32
msgid ""
"Scale back your involvement to a level you find sustainable over the long"
" term."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:33
msgid "Take a break altogether."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:36
msgid "Taking a break"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:37
msgid ""
"It's *completely* okay to stop your involvement for a time. Everyone "
"would prefer that you take a breather if it meant you could come back "
"refreshed and ready to pick things up again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:41
#: ../../organizer/eventhosting/events.rst:4
msgid "Events"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:43
msgid ""
"Have variety! Try different speakers, different topics, difference "
"venues. Intersperse large events with simpler, informal ones. Lightning "
"talks help break things up."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:44
msgid ""
"Work with other groups in your community, ask them to lend a hand with "
"things from time to time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:49
msgid "Coping with burnout"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:52
msgid "If you notice someone seems to be burning out"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:54
msgid ""
"Meet with them, outside of an official event, in a relaxed environment. "
"Learn how they are feeling, work with them to determine how to deal with "
"it if they *are* burning out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:56
msgid ""
"Let them take a breather and leave them the option to leave permanently "
"without guilt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:59
msgid "If you are feeling burnt out"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:60
msgid ""
"Know that you are not alone. This stuff is hard, and it's hard to do for "
"a long time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:61
msgid "It's ok to ask people to step up and help more."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:62
msgid "Reach out to other PyLadies group organizers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:63
msgid "Again: It's ok to take a break."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:67
msgid "Why are you here?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:69
msgid ""
"Think about your personal goals and how your work is helpign you achieve "
"them. Also think about how your goals might be better achieved if, in the"
" long term, you maanged to avoid burning out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:70
msgid ""
"It's really rewarding to help women both learn Python and find their "
"place in the larger community, but it's really hard work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:71
msgid ""
"There's more support in your group than you might guess. People will want"
" to help you out if they can."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:74
#: ../../organizer/eventhosting/grant-proposals/sample-hackathon.rst:59
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:76
msgid "Self care is important, perhaps most important."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:78
msgid ""
"In particular, in times of stress, illness, or sleep-deprivation, "
"remember to take the time to show compassion and care for *yourself*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:80
msgid "People are human."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:82
msgid ""
"We all get sick, overwhelmed, forgetful, and make mistakes at times. Try "
"to remember and embrace these as the \"oh, goodness\" moments of "
"volunteering."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:84
msgid "\"Hello, Murphy. Welcome.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/burnout.rst:86
msgid ""
"Murphy's Law (Source: Wikipedia. an adage or epigram that is typically "
"stated as: Anything that can go wrong will go wrong.) pops up in the most"
" unexpected times and places. Accept Murphy works in mysterious, "
"unpredictable ways. A sense of humor, humility, and resourcefulness are "
"crucial to effective community organizing."
msgstr ""

