msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:62
msgid "Receiving a Complaint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:64
msgid ""
"Ask the reporter to write down what happened to the best of their "
"ability. If the report was given verbally or does not want to, then "
"please write down the complaint yourself (see :ref:`record`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:66
msgid "We suggest the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:68
msgid "Identifying information of the participant doing the harassing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:69
msgid "The behavior that was in violation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:70
msgid ""
"The approximate time of the behavior (if different than the time of the "
"report was made)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:71
msgid "Any circumstances surrounding the incident"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:72
msgid "Other people involved in the incident"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:73
msgid "If they wish to remain anonymous in any way"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:74
msgid "How you can contact them for follow up"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:76
msgid ""
"We suggest to have a designated person (*not* the whole group of "
"organizers) to handle the conversation between the involved parties and "
"the local group.  This is to avoid the \"group against one\" environment,"
" as well as \"interviewing\" or otherwise \"evidence gathering\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:78
msgid ""
"Make it known to the parties involved about who is a part of the group "
"that addresses these complaints (if it's just you, or other organizers "
"will be brought in to discuss how to handle the complaint), and that you "
"will be documenting the report and the response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:81
msgid "Responding to a Complaint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:83
msgid ""
"There are various levels of responses depending on the incident.  Please "
"follow accordingly:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:87
msgid "Threats to Physical Wellbeing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:89
msgid ""
"Most harassment complaints aren't of this nature, but if someone reports "
"that an attendee has committed or is threatening violence towards another"
" attendee, or other safety issues:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:91
msgid ""
"If there is any general threat to attendees or the safety of anyone "
"including conference staff is in doubt, summon security or police."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:92
msgid "Offer the victim a private place to sit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:93
msgid ""
"Ask \"is there a friend or trusted person who you would like to be with "
"you?\" (if so, arrange for someone to fetch this person)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:94
msgid "Ask them \"how can I help?\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:95
msgid "Provide them with your :ref:`emergency` if they need help later"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:98
msgid "Law Enforcement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:100
msgid ""
"If everyone is presently physically safe, involve law enforcement or "
"security only at a victim's request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:102
msgid ""
"In many cases, reporting harassment to law enforcement is very unpleasant"
" and may result in further harassment. Forcing victims to go to law "
"enforcement will reduce reports of harassment (but not actual "
"harassment). For more information, see Why Didn't You Report It?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:104
msgid ""
"An organizer can provide the :ref:`emergency` and say something like \"if"
" you want any help reporting this incident, please let us know\" and "
"leave it at that."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:107
msgid "Reports of Harassment that were Widely Witnessed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:108
msgid ""
"These include things like harassing content in talks, or harassment that "
"took place in a crowded space."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:110
msgid ""
"Simply say \"Thanks, this sounds like a breach of our :ref:`coc`. I am "
"going to convene a meeting of a small group of people and figure out what"
" our response will be.\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:113
msgid "Reports of more private harassment"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:115
msgid ""
"Offer the reporter/victim a chance to decide if any further action is "
"taken: \"OK, this sounds like a breach of our :ref:`coc` policy. If "
"you're OK with it I am going to convene a meeting of a small group of "
"people and figure out what our response will be.\" Pause, and see if they"
" say they do not want this. Otherwise, go ahead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:118
msgid "Things not to do"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:120
msgid ""
"Do not overtly invite them to withdraw the complaint or mention that "
"withdrawal is OK: this suggests that you want them to do so, and is "
"therefore coercive. \"If you're OK with it [pursuing the complaint]\" "
"suggests that you are by default pursuing it and is not coercive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:121
msgid ""
"Do not ask for their advice on how to deal with the complaint: this is "
"the staff's responsibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:122
msgid "Do not offer them input into penalties: this is the staff's responsibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:123
msgid ""
"Do not share details of the people involved or incident without specific "
"permission from the victim. This includes sharing with other organizers "
"(unless they are a part of your group to respond to incidents."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:127
msgid "Forming a Response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:129
msgid ""
"You should aim to take action **as soon as reasonably possible**. During "
"the event, a response within the next half-day is usually an appropriate "
"timeframe. After the event you may need more time to gather sufficient "
"decision makers, but ideally responding within the same week or sooner is"
" good."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:132
msgid "Meeting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:133
msgid ""
"Available co-organizers should meet as soon as possible after a report to"
" discuss:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:135
msgid "What happened?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:136
msgid "Are we doing anything about it?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:137
msgid "Who is doing those things?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:138
msgid "When are they doing them?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:140
msgid ""
"Neither the complainant nor the alleged harasser should attend. (If the "
"event was very widely witnessed, such as a harassing talk, this may be an"
" exception to this guideline.) People with a conflict of interest should "
"exclude themselves or if necessary be excluded by others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:143
msgid "Communicate with the alleged harasser about the complaint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:145
msgid ""
"As soon as possible, either before or during the above meeting, let the "
"alleged harasser know that there is a complaint about them, let them tell"
" someone their side of the story and that person takes it into the "
"meeting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:148
msgid "Communicate with the harasser about the response"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:149
msgid ""
"As soon as possible after that meeting, let the harasser know what action"
" is being taken. Give them a place to appeal to if there is one, but in "
"the meantime the action stands. \"If you'd like to discuss this further, "
"please contact XYZ, but in the meantime, you must <something something>\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:153
msgid "Possible sanctions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:155
msgid ""
"Your guiding principle should be the **safety of your community members "
"from harassment** and you should evaluate sanctions in light of whether "
"they provide the safety needed. You and your event are the only people "
"who can judge appropriate sanctions in your community based on the nature"
" of the incident and the responses of the people involved, but some "
"possibilities are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:157
msgid ""
"Warning the harasser to cease their behaviour and that any further "
"reports will result in sanctions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:158
msgid ""
"Requiring that the harasser avoid any interaction with, and physical "
"proximity to, their victim for the remainder of the event"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:159
msgid "Ending a talk that violates the policy early"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:160
msgid "Not publishing the video or slides of a talk that violated the policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:161
msgid ""
"Not allowing a speaker who violated the policy to give (further) talks at"
" the event"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:162
msgid ""
"Immediately ending any event volunteer responsibilities and privileges "
"the harasser holds"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:163
msgid ""
"Requiring that the harasser not volunteer for future events your "
"organization runs (either indefinitely or for a certain time period)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:164
msgid ""
"Requiring that the harasser refund any travel grants and similar they "
"received (this would need to be a condition of the grant at the time of "
"being awarded)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:165
msgid "Requiring that the harasser immediately leave the event and not return"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:166
msgid ""
"Banning the harasser from future events (either indefinitely or for a "
"certain time period)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:167
msgid "Removing a harasser from membership of relevant organizations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:168
msgid ""
"Publishing an account of the harassment and calling for the resignation "
"of the harasser from their responsibilities (usually pursued by people "
"without formal authority: may be called for if the harasser is the event "
"leader, or refuses to stand aside from the conflict of interest, or "
"similar, typically event staff have sufficient governing rights over "
"their space that this isn't as useful)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:171
msgid "Employer reports"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:172
msgid ""
"If someone harassed someone else while in an official employee capacity, "
"such as while working as paid event staff, while giving a talk about "
"their employer's product, while staffing a sponsor booth, while wearing "
"their employer's branded merchandise, while attempting to recruit someone"
" for a job, or while claiming to represent their employer's views, it may"
" be appropriate to provide a short report of their conduct to their "
"employer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:175
msgid "Don't require or encourage apologies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:176
msgid ""
"We do not suggest asking for an apology to the victim. You have no "
"responsibility to enforce friendship, reconciliation, or anything beyond "
"lack of harassment between any two given attendees, and in fact doing so "
"can contribute to someone's lack of safety at your event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:178
msgid ""
"Forcing a victim of harassment to acknowledge an apology from their "
"harasser forces further contact with their harasser. It also creates a "
"social expectation that they will accept the apology, forgive their "
"harasser, and return their social connection to its previous status. A "
"person who has been harassed will often prefer to ignore or avoid their "
"harasser entirely. Bringing them together with a third party mediator and"
" other attempts to \"repair\" the situation which require further "
"interaction between them should likewise be avoided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../organizer/difficult/responding.rst:180
msgid ""
